   │   ▐    ░                                                               │
   │· ·▐                                                                    │
   │    ▌     The biggest release of the year concides with the biggest     │
   │    ▌     event of the year - ones birthday. Thats right, today we are  │
   │    ░     2 years old, and as last year, we give shouts to the fans &   │
   │          a big FU to the haters - luckily we have more of the          │
   │          former than the latter this time around. Things are looking   │
   │          up, so expect more good things from us in the future.         │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │   Release notes: I was dreading having to write this, but 4 hours of   │
   │   nothing going wrong is seemingly too much to ask for.                │
   │   It starts of with an audio "issue" - there are minor pops in the     │
   │   stream as this thing starts and goes on for around 4 mins. Nothing   │
   │   to kill the experience, we just want you to know that we know and    │
   │   that we didnt cause it (as far as we can tell). Then after that, we  │
   │   had a minor loss of signal for around 6 seconds, luckily not in the  │
   │   middle of anything important.                                        │
   │   Thats it for the bad things, as far as we know. The rest should      │
   │   prove to be as awsome as we have come to expect from ourselves and   │
   │   you from us - and it should be a little entertaining too, we hope.   │
   │   I mean, just look at this match line up - impressive innit? I really │
   │   hope this one isnt copied over to certain others nfos should they be │
   │   releasing a version in any other formats.. thats just low, we feel.  │
   │   Anyway, enough babbling, go watch it damnit!                         │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                      WWE WrestleMania 22 Preview                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                            WWE Championship                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                     Champion John Cena Vs Triple H                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Since prior to the Royal Rumble, Triple H has targeted WM 22 in     │
   │    Chicago as the time and place for the ôKing of Kingsö to regain     │
   │    his throne. To get there, the 10-time world champion had to battle  │
   │    through the Road to WrestleMania Tournament, last dispatching of    │
   │    Rob Van Dam and Big Show in the Triple Threat finals.               │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    In doing so, The Game accomplished the first of his goals:          │
   │    securing a main event, WWE Championship Match at WrestleMania.      │
   │    Next, the Cerebral Assassin will have to devise a way to defeat     │
   │    resilient champion John Cena.                                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    While Triple H settled scores with the likes of Ric Flair and       │
   │    Big Show, John Cena battled against all odds ù week after week ù    │
   │    for almost a year to hold onto his gold. That run was finally       │
   │    stopped by Edge's well-timed ômoney in the bank,ö but Cena bounced  │
   │    back with more intensity and desire than ever and immediately       │
   │    recaptured the WWE Championship.                                    │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Both Triple H and John Cena were put to the test on the March 6     │
   │    edition of RAW. They both participated in WrestleMania Rewind       │
   │    Matches in which they faced former WrestleMania opponents. HHH      │
   │    faced Kane, and thanks to some interference from Carlito and        │
   │    Chris Masters, The Game was able to pick up a victory.              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Cena had the daunting task of taking on his WrestleMania twenty     │
   │    opponent, Big Show. Cena managed to overcome the big size           │
   │    differential and even hoisted the mammoth Big Show up for a         │
   │    thunderous FU. The maneuver even impressed Triple H who was         │
   │    watching from outside the ring.                                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    One week later they made their WrestleMania match official during   │
   │    a contract signing on RAW. The two got into a war of words, but     │
   │    before a physical confrontation could escalate Big Show & Kane came │
   │    to the ring as well as Carlito and Masters. Cena had his back       │
   │    turned to Triple H amidst the chaos, and The Game picked up a       │
   │    sledgehammer that he had hidden underneath the table in the ring.   │
   │    Cena turned around before Triple H could take a swing, but the      │
   │    intensity was so thick you could cut it with a knife.               │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Later that night, Cena & Triple H were on opposite sides in a 6 man │
   │    tag team match. The Chump teamed up with World Tag Team Champions   │
   │    Kane & Big Show to take on Triple H, Carlito & Chris Masters. After │
   │    some heated action, Carlito and Masters nailed Kane and Big Show    │
   │    with steel chairs, causing a disqualification. Then, from out of    │
   │    nowhere, Randy Orton stormed the ring and hit Cena with an RKO.     │
   │    Orton's former mentor, Triple H, looked upset at first, but then    │
   │    an evil smile crept across his face.                                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Orton's attack was an effort to get an upperhand heading into       │
   │    Saturday Night's Main Event on March 18 on NBC.                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    After what happened on RAW, it was only fitting that the Handicap   │
   │    Tag Team Match came down to Orton and Cena. The Chump had things    │
   │    going his way, but Triple H broke up a pin attempt and Pedigreed    │
   │    his partner and WrestleMania opponent. He put Orton on top for the  │
   │    pin, but Rey Mysterio pulled him off, not wanting to win in such a  │
   │    fashion. Triple H Pedigreed Rey, but then Kurt Angle clotheselined  │
   │    The Game out of the ring. Orton came back and RKO'd Angle, but Cena │
   │    was able to counter another RKO & picked up the win with a roll up. │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    That Monday on RAW, Cena & Triple H found themselves on opposite    │
   │    sides of a tag team match. However, Cena was quickly disqualified   │
   │    for using a closed fist, giving HHH & Shane McMahon the victory     │
   │    over Cena & Shawn Michaels. The match was then made into a Handicap │
   │    Match, but no decision was rendered after Cena returned to help HBK │
   │    fend off Shane & The Game. An irate Mr. McMahon then announced that │
   │    Cena would face the WWE Chairman himself on March 27.               │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, Triple H took on Michaels.    │
   │    when it looked like HBK was ready to secure the victory, Mr.McMahon │
   │    interfered. Michaels fought him off, but walked right into Pedigree │
   │    from Triple H. The Game & the WWE Chairman then assaulted Michaels  │
   │    until John Cena made the save, prompting Mr. McMahon to announce    │
   │    that HBK and The Game would be at ringside for his match with Cena  │
   │    later that night.                                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    HBK and Triple H were handcuffed to the ropes for that match, which │
   │    ended when Mr. McMahon kicked Cena low, drawing a DQ. McMahon & The │
   │    Game then assaulted both Cena & Michaels; Triple H smashed Cena in  │
   │    the head with a sledgehammer, and the Chairman nailed HBK with a    │
   │    chair as he was still handcuffed. McMahon & Triple H then posed in  │
   │    the ring, standing over their bloodied WrestleMania opponents.      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    What will happen at WrestleMania 22? Will the ôKing of Kingsö come  │
   │    through on his bold declaration and be crowned an 11-time world     │
   │    champion, or will The Chump once again rise to the occasion on the  │
   │    biggest stage of them all?                                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                       World Heavyweight Champion                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │           Champion Kurt Angle Vs Rey Mysterio Vs Randy Orton           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    At WrestleMania 22, the World Heavyweight Championship will be      │
   │    decided in a Triple Threat Match.                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    At the Royal Rumble, Rey Mysterio last eliminated Randy Orton to    │
   │    win the Royal Rumble Match, earning a championship match in the     │
   │    main event at WrestleMania. Rey dedicated the victory to Eddie      │
   │    Guerrero, and this dedication would ultimately lead to him losing   │
   │    his opportunity.                                                    │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Randy Orton made some disparaging comments about Guerrero, but it   │
   │    was all a ploy. The Legend Killer wanted Rey's main event slot all  │
   │    along, and challenged Mysterio to a match for the opportunity.      │
   │    Because of Orton's slander of Guerrero, Rey accepted. However, at   │
   │    No Way Out, a handful of ropes helped Orton defeat Mysterio,        │
   │    claiming the prize Rey had won in the Royal Rumble Match.           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following Friday night, Rey apologized to everyone for letting  │
   │    them down by losing the opportunity. However, General Manager       │
   │    Theodore Long interrupted his speech; he told Rey that while he     │
   │    couldn't take Orton out of the main event, he could add to it, and  │
   │    announced that the main event of WrestleMania 22 would be a Triple  │
   │    Threat Match, with both the Legend Killer and Mysterio challenging  │
   │    the World Heavyweight Champion.                                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    As for the final slot in the match, it will be Kurt Angle. Kurt     │
   │    Angle faced Undertaker in a No Way Out rematch on the March 3       │
   │    edition of SmackDown. After missing a moonsault, Undertaker was     │
   │    able to connect with a Tombstone and it looked like the Deadman     │
   │    would be the new World Heavyweight Champion. But Mark Henry stormed │
   │    the ring and broke up the pin. The interference gave Undertaker the │
   │    win, but Angle retained the gold since the Championship cannot      │
   │    change hands via diqualification.                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    One week later, Mysterio and Angle, despite facing each other at    │
   │    WrestleMania, teamed up to take on Orton and Henry in a blockbuster │
   │    tag team match. Angle and Mysterio seemed to work well together as  │
   │    a team, but things broke down as the match wore on. The World's     │
   │    Strongest Man savagely attacked the referee, and all hell broke     │
   │    loose. Henry appeared poised to splash Rey through a table, but     │
   │    Angle made the save. Orton then attacked the World Heavyweight      │
   │    Champion and laid him down on the table. The Legend Killer then     │
   │    directed Mark Henry to come off the middle rope, splashing Angle    │
   │    through the table.                                                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    But before these three Superstars can even get to WrestleMania,     │
   │    they will be forced to team up with each other to take on WWE       │
   │    Champion John Cena and Triple H in a RAW WrestleMania main event Vs │
   │    SmackDown main event match at Saturday Night's Main Event. They had │
   │    a bit of a warmup on Friday Night SmackDown on March 17, and were   │
   │    able to defeat MNM & Mark Henry. However, Orton never tagged into   │
   │    the match, instead waiting until Mysterio nailed Joey Mercury with  │
   │    a 619 to get involved. At that point, the Legend Killer tagged in,  │
   │    tossed Rey to the floor, and made the pinfall on Mercury.           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    With so much bad blood and emotion among the three Superstars, it   │
   │    was no surprise that they couldn't coexist as a team at Saturday    │
   │    Night's Main Event. The RAW side couldn't get along either. HHH     │
   │    nailed John Cena with a Pedigree & Orton went for the pin. Mysterio │
   │    didn't want to win that way, so he pulled the Legend Killer off     │
   │    Cena. Triple H Pedigreed Mysterio as a result, but Angle knocked    │
   │    The Game out of the ring. Orton came back & hit Angle with an RKO,  │
   │    but Cena was able to roll up the Legend Killer for the win.         │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the following Friday Night SmackDown, Orton cost both of his     │
   │    opponents their matches. First, he gave Mysterio an RKO, allowing   │
   │    Finaly to pick up a victory. (Watch video) Later in the night, he   │
   │    attempted to interfere in Angle's match with Mark Henry; Mysterio   │
   │    tried to stop him but accidentally hit Angle with a West Coast Pop, │
   │    allowing Henry to get the pin. Angle & Mysterio argued after the    │
   │    match, and the World Heavyweight Champion ended up on the receiving │
   │    end of a 619.                                                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    But after the last stop on the Road to WrestleMania, the Wrestling  │
   │    Machine looked unstoppable. Angle went one on one with Rey Mysterio │
   │    in the SmackDown main event. Randy Orton had been barred from the   │
   │    arena to insure a fair match with no interference. Mysterio looked  │
   │    like he had things going his way and went for the 619, but Angle    │
   │    was able to catch him in mid-maneuver and turned it into an ankle   │
   │    lock. Mysterio tapped out and the Wrestling Machine was victorious. │
   │    After Angle left the ring, Orton entered and nailed Mysterio with   │
   │    an RKO. A sly grin crept across Angle's face, but Orton told him to │
   │    stop smiling because at WrestleMania he would suffer the same fate. │
   │    The Olympic Gold Medalist stormed the ring, but Orton stopped him   │
   │    in his tracks. The Legend Killer went for an RKO, but Angle reversed│
   │    it into an Angle Slam. He then trapped him in the ankle lock, and   │
   │    even though it wasn't a real match, Orton tapped out.               │
   │    Could this be a sign of things to come at WrestleMania 22?          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Who will emerge from Chicago as the World Heavyweight Champion? Can │
   │    Orton fulfill his proclaimed destiny and regain the gold? Can Rey   │
   │    take home the gold in memory of his beloved friend? Or will the     │
   │    Olympic Gold Medalist stay golden through April 2?                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                            No Holds Barred                             │
   │                                                                        │
   │                     Mr. McMahon Vs. Shawn Michaels                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Since the night after Christmas, Mr. McMahon has made it his        │
   │    mission to make Shawn Michaels' life a living hell. At WM 22        │
   │    HBK will get a chance to get some retribution when he meets the     │
   │    WWE Chairman one on one.                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Dec. 26, 2005 edition of RAW, HBK told Mr. McMahon to get    │
   │    over the Montreal Incident; Shawn's comments irked the WWE chairman │
   │    who told HBK that if he didn't watch his step, he'd get screwed     │
   │    worse than Bret Hart ever did.                                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Over the next few weeks, Mr. McMahon did everything he could to     │
   │    throw HBK off his game, including banning Sweet Chin Music during   │
   │    one match. However, the biggest blow came at the Royal Rumble,      │
   │    when Shane McMahon made a surprise appearance and eliminated HBK    │
   │    from the Royal Rumble Match. Shane struck again the next night      │
   │    on RAW, attacking HBK with a chair as he jawed with his father.     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    In subsequent weeks, Mr. McMahon continued to toy with Shawn,       │
   │    taking him out of the Road to WrestleMania Tournament & announcing  │
   │    a mandatory Shawn Michaels Retirement Party, where HBK would be     │
   │    forced to walk away from WWE forever. Instead of signing his        │
   │    retirement papers, though, HBK ripped them up and threw them in     │
   │    McMahon's face.                                                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The next week, Mr. McMahon made Michaels take on four members of    │
   │    the Spirit Squad in a Handicap Match. After the Spirit Squad got    │
   │    disqualified, HBK's former partner Marty Jannetty made a            │
   │    surprising return to help Shawn fend off a 5-on-1 attack.           │
   │    Mr. McMahon announced later that night that he would offer          │
   │    Jannetty a full-time WWE contract, but Marty would have to kiss     │
   │    his ass to get it.                                                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 27 edition of RAW, the WWE Chairman offered Marty the   │
   │    contract. When Marty wouldn't kiss his ass, he called out Chris     │
   │    Masters, telling Jannetty that he would get the contract if he      │
   │    could escape the Master Lock. As the Masterpiece had the hold       │
   │    locked on, Mr. McMahon made him bring Marty down to kiss his ass.   │
   │    HBK interrupted, hitting Masters with Sweet Chin Music and stalking │
   │    the WWE Chairman, whose pants were still around his ankles. Before  │
   │    he got to him, however, Shane McMahon attacked HBK from behind &    │
   │    laid him out with a chairshot.                                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    As Mr.McMahon berated an unconscious HBK, he announced that Michaels│
   │    would take on Shane in a Street Fight at SNME. After Shane made the │
   │    defenseless HBK kiss his father's ass, Mr. McMahon then said he     │
   │    would kick Shawn's ass at WrestleMania as well.                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week, HBK tried to attack the McMahons during a       │
   │    speech. Instead, Mr. McMahon announced that HBK would meet Shane    │
   │    that night on RAW. (Watch video) Prior to the match, Stephanie      │
   │    McMahon set up HBK, slipping something in his drink that caused     │
   │    him to become ill. This made him easy prey for Shane, who easily    │
   │    pinned Michaels. To add insult to injury, Mr. McMahon then made     │
   │    and won a match against HBK immediately afterward.                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 13 edition of RAW, Mr. McMahon made Michaels take a    │
   │    public urination test as a result of the previous week. Things went │
   │    bad, and HBK ended up throwing his cup of urine onto the McMahons.  │
   │    Mr. McMahon put HBK in a Steel Cage Match against the Spirit Squad  │
   │    as punishment, and Shane interfered to make sure the Spirit Squad   │
   │    got the victory. After the match, Shane grabbed a garbage can and   │
   │    drove it into the already bloodied HBK's head, courtesy of a        │
   │    coast-to-coast Van Terminator.                                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Before Shawn could even get to WrestleMania, he had to face Shane   │
   │    at SNME in a Street Fight. In a breath-taking, death-defying        │
   │    maneuver, HBK suplexed Shane off a ladder in the ring to the        │
   │    outside through a pair of tables. The Showstopper looked poised     │
   │    to pick up a victory after some Sweet Chin Music, but Mr. McMahon   │
   │    intervened and saved his son. Following a low blow, Shane lokced    │
   │    in a Sharpshooter, and Mr. McMahon immediately called for the bell  │
   │    in a moment all-too-similar to the Montreal incident in 1997. It    │
   │    was then that Mr. McMahon screwed Bret "Hit Man" Hart and it was    │
   │    now that he screwed HBK.                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Two nights later on RAW, Mr. McMahon made the WrestleMania match a  │
   │    No Holda Barred Match, and announced that the main event of RAW     │
   │    would be HBK & John Cena against Triple H & Shane. Cena was quickly │
   │    disqualified for using a closed fist, and Mr. McMahon threw him out │
   │    of the match, announcing a new match instead: HBK vs. Shane & The   │
   │    Game in a Handicap Match. HBK fought valiantly, but just as it      │
   │    looked like he would succumb to the Pedigree, Cena returned to help │
   │    HBK and the match was declared a no-contest.                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, HBK took on Triple H. when it │
   │    looked like HBK was ready to secure the victory, Mr. McMahon        │
   │    interfered. Michaels fought him off, but walked right into a        │
   │    Pedigree from Triple H. The Game & the WWE Chairman then assaulted  │
   │    Michaels until John Cena made the save, prompting Mr. McMahon to    │
   │    announce that HBK and The Game would be at ringside for his match   │
   │    with Cena later that night.                                         │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    HBK and Triple H were handcuffed to the ropes for that match, which │
   │    ended when Mr. McMahon kicked Cena low, drawing a DQ. McMahon &     │
   │    The Game then assaulted both Cena & Michaels, with the Chairman     │
   │    nailing HBK with a chair as he was still handcuffed. McMahon &      │
   │    Triple H then posed in the ring, standing over their bloodied       │
   │    WrestleMania opponents.                                             │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Will Michaels have enough gas left in the tank to finally get the   │
   │    best of the McMahons, or will the WWE Chairman triumph on April 2?  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                              Casket Match                              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                        Undertaker Vs Mark Henry                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The Deadman's WrestleMania streak is well-documented. The most      │
   │    successful Superstar in WrestleMania history is an astounding       │
   │    13-0 on the grandest stage of them all. But that can all change     │
   │    at WrestleMania 22. Year after year, Superstar after Superstar      │
   │    tries to bring the amazing streak to an end, but this could         │
   │    finally be the year as the World's Strongest Man takes on           │
   │    Undertaker in a Casket Match.                                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    At first glance, it might appear that Undertaker has an enormous    │
   │    advantage heading into the Super Bowl of professional wrestling.    │
   │    He is undefeated after all, and this is one of his signature        │
   │    matches. It's as if he has the home field advantage. But he's       │
   │    not facing any ordinary opponent. He's facing the human wrecking    │
   │    machine, Mark Henry.                                                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Henry burst back onto the scene in December, attacking then-World   │
   │    Heavyweight Champion Batista. Within weeks he had brutalized the    │
   │    Champion so badly, he knocked him out of commission with a triceps  │
   │    injury. He then came within inches of defeating Kurt Angle for      │
   │    the World Heavyweight Championship. The Wrestling Machine needed    │
   │    a steel chair and exposed turnbuckle to fend off the World's        │
   │    Strongest Man. After such an impressive showing, Henry felt he      │
   │    deserved a rematch. But that match went to Undertaker instead.      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Undertaker and Angle went on to have a classic encounter at NWO.    │
   │    Undertaker seemed to have the World Heavyweight Champion down and   │
   │    out in a triangle choke, but Angle was able to reverse it into a    │
   │    pinning combination for the pin. While the Deadman & the Wrestling  │
   │    Machine were putting on a wrestling clinic, though, Mark Henry's    │
   │    anger and frustration continued to build.                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    So, when Undertaker received a rematch two weeks later on Friday    │
   │    Night SmackDown, it was no surprise that all of Henry's emotion     │
   │    finally erupted. Angle missed a moonsault, so Undertaker went in    │
   │    for the kill and hit the Tombstone. Before the referee could make   │
   │    a three-count, however, the World's Strongest Man stormed the ring  │
   │    and attacked the Phenom.                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Henry had cost Undertaker the World Heavyweight Championship, but   │
   │    he wasn't done with the Deadman yet. He continued assaulting him    │
   │    outside the ring and set him up on the announce table. Henry then   │
   │    climbed up on the Spanish announce table, but it looked like he was │
   │    having second thoughts. He backed away from the edge of the table,  │
   │    but it turned out that it was just to get a running start. With a   │
   │    head of steam, Henry leapt off the Spanish announce table onto      │
   │    Undertaker and through the SmackDown announce table.                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    One week later, Henry opened up SmackDown, exclaiming that he       │
   │    refuses to be forgotten. He called out Kurt Angle, wanting an       │
   │    opportunity at the World Heavyweight Championship. Angle, never     │
   │    one to back down from a challenge, came to the ring. Within         │
   │    moments, Randy Orton and Rey Mysterio joined the fray, and General  │
   │    Manager Theodore Long threw them all in a tag team match later in   │
   │    the show. Henry showed his dominance once againàand his temper.     │
   │    As the match wore on, Henry grew frustrated and took it out on      │
   │    senior official Nick Patrick, flattening him with a thunderous      │
   │    avalanche. Daivari brought a table into the ring and Henry looked   │
   │    ready to squash Mysterio. Angle made the save, but then Orton       │
   │    caught him from behind and put the champ on the table. Henry knew   │
   │    what to do next and leapt off the middle rope, crashing down on     │
   │    Angle and threw the table. But almost immediately after Henry's     │
   │    impressive splash, the lights went out and the gong sounded. Fog    │
   │    began to fill the arena and Undertaker's ominous voice rang         │
   │    throughout. He simply stated, ôYou. Me. WrestleMania Casket         │
   │    Match.ö Most men would tremble at fear at the thought of facing     │
   │    the Deadman in such a match, let alone at WrestleMania, but not     │
   │    Mark Henry. The World's Strongest Man seemed ready for the          │
   │    challenge, and was not afraid of the Phenom.                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Henry didn't want to wair until WrestleMania to confront the        │
   │    Deadman, though. So, at Saturday Night's Main Event, the World's    │
   │    Strongest Man called out Undertaker. But always be careful what     │
   │    you ask for. The Phenom responded, and his druids brought a casket  │
   │    to the ring. Undertaker threw Henry into the ring steps and kicked  │
   │    him into the crowd. He continued to send a message when he          │
   │    delivered a thunderous Tombstone to Daivari on top of the casket.   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the last stop on the Road to WrestleMania, Mark Henry reiterated │
   │    that he is not afraid of the Deadman. He held a mock funeral and    │
   │    ran down the list of past WrestleMania victims who had fallen at    │
   │    the hands of Undertaker including the likes of Jake "The Snake"     │
   │    Roberts, Jimmy "Superfly" Snuka, Big Show and Kane. Henry said that │
   │    he's not like them. He was the one that took out Batista, he pinned │
   │    the World Heavyweight Champion and he said he will end Undertakers  │
   │    undefeated WrestleMania streak.                                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Can Mark Henry bring Undertaker's unprecedented WrestleMania        │
   │    winning streak to an end? Or will the Deadman make it an            │
   │    unbelievable 14-0?                                                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                     Money in the Bank Ladder Match                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                  RVD Vs Shelton Benjamin Vs Ric Flair                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │              Vs Fit Finlay Vs Bobby Lashley Vs Matt Hardy              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Last year at WrestleMania 21, Edge defeated five other RAW          │
   │    Superstars to win the first-ever Money in the Bank Ladder Match,    │
   │    earning a contract to face the WWE Champion anytime in the next     │
   │    year. This year, Money in the Bank returns to WrestleMania, and     │
   │    another Superstar will walk out of Chicago on April 2 with a        │
   │    guaranteed championship opportunity.                                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 20 edition of RAW, Carlito announced during his match   │
   │    that he had an idea for WrestleMania that was ôMoney in the Bank.ö  │
   │    The next week, Carlito announced that he pitched the idea to        │
   │    Mr. McMahon, who approved it and sanctioned another Money in the    │
   │    Bank Ladder Match for WrestleMania 22.                              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 27 RAW, 3 qualifying matches were held to determine who │
   │    would go on to WrestleMania, but no one knew who their opponent     │
   │    would be until the match began. In the first qualifier, RVD         │
   │    defeated Trevor Murdoch with the Five-Star Frog Splash. In the 2nd  │
   │    match, Intercontinental Champion and 2005 Money in the Bank         │
   │    participant Shelton Benjamin qualified when he pinned Chavo         │
   │    Guerrero after Randy Orton nailed Chavo with an RKO.                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Carlito then came out for the final qualifier of the night, and     │
   │    ôNature Boyö Ric Flair was announced as his opponent. Late in the   │
   │    match, Carlito appeared to have the berth secured when he went to   │
   │    ringside looking for an apple. As he climbed back inside the ring   │
   │    and prepared to spit in Flair's face, the Nature Boy kicked         │
   │    Carlito, forcing him to choke on the apple. Flair then rolled       │
   │    Carlito up, and with the help of the ropes, pinned him to become    │
   │    the third entrant into the match.                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On WWE.com Unlimited during the March 6 RAW, SmackDown General      │
   │    Manager Theodore Long interrupted an interview with Rob Van Dam     │
   │    to make a shocking announcement. Long said that the Money in the    │
   │    Bank Match will be an inter-promotional one, and he set the         │
   │    qualifying matches to begin on the March 10 edition of Friday Night │
   │    SmackDown.                                                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Since then, RVD, Flair & benjamin have been at each others throats. │
   │    On the March 13 RAW, Flair inadvertently cost RVD a match with      │
   │    Benjamin for the Intercontinental Championship. The next week, all  │
   │    three men were involved in a Triple Threat Match for the gold; in   │
   │    an unusual finish, Benjamin retained the gold when he pinned Flair  │
   │    while the Nature Boy had RVD in the Figure-Four Leg Lock.           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, Flair came to the ring to     │
   │    talk about his plans to win the match. Shelton Benjamin interrupted │
   │    and a brawl broke out between the two. RVD made the save for Flair, │
   │    nailing the Intercontinental Champion with Rolling Thunder on a     │
   │    ladder. RVD then reminded both of them that it would be every man   │
   │    for himself at WM, prompting Flair to nail RVD with a ladder.       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the SmackDown side of things, qualifying has been just as crazy. │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    SmackDown's first qualifier matched the rough and tough Finlay      │
   │    against impressive newcomer Lashley. The previous week, the two     │
   │    Superstars had a match, but a winner was never determined. Instead, │
   │    Lashley and Finlay swung chairs at each other causing a double-dq.  │
   │    With so much riding on the match, it was no surprise when it broke  │
   │    down as well. In fact, the match never even started.                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Before Lashley could get into the ring, he and Finlay clashed head  │
   │    on. Officials and security swarmed and tried to separate them again │
   │    but the two brawled all the way out to the parking lot. Finlay      │
   │    bashed Lashley with a steel pipe, but Lashley came back and bashed  │
   │    Finlay's head into a car eight times. With Finlay laying on top of  │
   │    the car, Lashley attempted to do the unthinkable. The hard-hitting, │
   │    soft-spoken monster began pushing the car over. Security tried to   │
   │    stop him, but Lashley would not be denied. Showing superhuman       │
   │    strength, Lashley was able to tip the car completely over. Before   │
   │    he did so, though, Finlay was fortunate enough to roll off the car, │
   │    otherwise he would have been crushed.                               │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week, the two met again, this time in a Lumberjack    │
   │    Match. Thanks to his trusty shillelagh, Finlay was able to defeat   │
   │    Lashley to become the fourth qualifier. Also that night, Matt Hardy │
   │    became the fifth qualifier, defeating Road Warrior Animal by dq     │
   │    after the referee found brass knuckles on Animal and reversed his   │
   │    original decision.                                                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The final qualifier was determined on the March 24 edition of       │
   │    Friday Night SmackDown, as 20 men entered a Last Chance Battle      │
   │    Royal for the final spot. It came down to Lashley and MNM as the    │
   │    final three, and after the WWE Tag Team Champions botched a         │
   │    double-team, Lashley picked up Mercury in a gorilla press. He       │
   │    tossed Mercury into Nitro, sending both men tumbling over the top   │
   │    rope to give Lashley the victory and the final spot.                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Who will follow in Edge's footsteps and become Mr. Money in the     │
   │    Bank at WrestleMania 22?                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                             Hardcore Match                             │
   │                                                                        │
   │                           Edge Vs Mick Foley                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    In his WWE career, Edge has been involved in some of the most       │
   │    memorable WrestleMania matches, and has won them all. At WM 22      │
   │    he hopes to continue that trend when he steps into Mick Foley's     │
   │    domain, taking on the Hardcore Legend in a Hardcore Match.          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 16 edition of RAW, Foley was the referee for Edge's     │
   │    WWE Championship Match against John Cena. After the Rated R         │
   │    Superstar was defeated, he blamed the Hardcore Legend for the       │
   │    loss, spearing him in the middle of the ring. The next week,        │
   │    after defeating ôHacksawö Jim Duggan on RAW, Edge issued a WM       │
   │    challenge to Foley, saying he would go to Foley's home to get an    │
   │    answer if he didn't show up the next week.                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 27 RAW, Foley declined Edge's challenge of a            │
   │    traditional match, instead offering a Hardcore Match on April 2.    │
   │    Foley then rushed the ring with a barbed-wire baseball bat,         │
   │    sending Edge & Lita scurrying from the ring.                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week, as Edge was prepared to spear Maria, Foley ran  │
   │    in to brawl with the Rated R Superstar. Edge was able to come out   │
   │    on top, spearing Foley and delivering a one-man Conchairto. As      │
   │    Foley lay beaten in the ring, Edge then announced that he accepted  │
   │    Foley's Hardcore challenge.                                         │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 13 RAW, Edge mocked Mick Foley with a series of movie  │
   │    style trailers. Edge also announced that his talk show, ôThe        │
   │    Cutting Edge,ö would return at Saturday Night's Main Event with     │
   │    special guest Mick Foley.                                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Before Edge brought Foley out for the Cutting Edge, the Rated R     │
   │    Superstar belittled his WrestleMania opponent, basically saying     │
   │    that he has become a shell of his former self. But the Hardcore     │
   │    Legend responded in typical hardcore fashion. Edge tried to fend    │
   │    off Foley with a flaming table, but Foley stormed right through &   │
   │    tried to use a bag of thumb tacks. Edge was able to turn the tables │
   │    though, & bulldogged the Hardcore Legend face-first into the tacks. │
   │    Foley, however, actually seemed to enjoy being in the tacks. The    │
   │    Hardcore Legend seemed rejuvenated and chased Edge up the ramp.     │
   │    Foley exacted a measure of revenge from the previous week when he   │
   │    bashed Edge's skull with a con-chair-to of his own.                 │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following Monday on RAW, Foley announced that the old Hardcore  │
   │    Legend was back. Lita came out to try to persuade him to give Edge  │
   │    clemency, but Foley instead instructed her to slap him. Edge then   │
   │    tried to attack Foley from behind, but Mick put Lita in the         │
   │    Mandible Claw to keep him at bay.                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, Foley came out to apologize   │
   │    for hurting Lita. He brought Edge a gift, which turned out to be a  │
   │    baseball bat. Foley told Edge to use it at WrestleMania so that he  │
   │    would have a fighting chance; instead, Edge tried to use it right   │
   │    away, but the Hardcore Legend produced a barbed-wire baseball bat   │
   │    of his own to keep Edge & Lita at bay.                              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Last year at WrestleMania 21, Edge became Mr. Money in the Bank.    │
   │    Can he come out on top at WrestleMania once again, or will Foley    │
   │    prove that he's still the only Hardcore Legend in WWE?              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                       United States Championship                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │            Champion Chris Benoit Vs. John Bradshaw Layfield            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Chris Benoit and JBL are two of the toughest Superstars in WWE      │
   │    history. The Rabid Wolverine has shown time & time again that he    │
   │    has ruthless aggression, and JBL has proven that he can trade       │
   │    blows with the best of them. Add Benoit's United States             │
   │    Championship to the equation and you have all the makings of a      │
   │    brutal brawl. And that was before things became personal.           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the Feb. 24 edition of SmackDown, Chris Benoit teamed up with    │
   │    Lashley and Rey Mysterio to take on JBL, Lashley and Randy Orton.   │
   │    Benoit and JBL ended up on the outside of the ring, and the Rabid   │
   │    Wolverine went in for the kill. He sandwiched JBLs hand in between  │
   │    the ring steps and the ring post. Then he backed up, gathered a     │
   │    head of steam and smashed the steps into JBL's hand, crushing it    │
   │    against the post. To make sure he had done enough damage, Benoit    │
   │    geared up and slammed the steps once again as JBL screamed out in   │
   │    pain. Not only did Benoit's team end up picking up the win, but     │
   │    JBL landed on the operating table due to a broken hand.             │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    JBL sent a message to Benoit on the March 17 edition of FNS,        │
   │    however. After Benoit made Jordan tap out to the Sharpshooter, JBL  │
   │    left the announce table and got in the ring, nailing Benoit with    │
   │    a beer cooler.                                                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    JBL had his hands full with Stone Cold Steve Austin at Saturday     │
   │    Night's Main Event in a Beer Drinking Contest. The Wrestling God    │
   │    tried to cheat his way to a win by spilling his beer instead of     │
   │    drinking it, but the Texas Rattlesnake caught him in the act. JBL   │
   │    tossed a beer at Stone Cold & tried to retreat, but Benoit ran out  │
   │    and threw the media maven back into the ring for a Stunner.         │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week on Friday Night SmackDown, JBL said that he      │
   │    would go out and face Benoit, but he wasn't cleared with his broken │
   │    hand. Instead, he recruited William Regal to face the Rabid         │
   │    Wolverine. Things didn't work out in JBL's favor, however, as the   │
   │    United States Champion made Regal tap out to the Crippler Crossface.│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    JBL has vowed to beat Chris Benoit on the grandest stage of them    │
   │    all. Can JBL get some revenge on the Rabid Wolverine and win his    │
   │    first United States Championship as a result?                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                       World Tag Team Championship                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │          Champions Big Show & Kane Vs Chris Masters & Carlito          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    In recent months, Kane & Big Show have had issues with Chris        │
   │    Masters & Carlito. At WrestleMania 22, the World Tag Team Champions │
   │    will put their gold on the line against the two young lions.        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    This past February, Kane defeated Masters in a singles match on     │
   │    RAW. After the bout, however, Masters attacked the Big Red Monster  │
   │    from behind, cinching in the Master Lock. It was also Masters &     │
   │    Carlito who teamed up to eliminate Kane in the Elimination Chamber  │
   │    Match at New Year's Revolution.                                     │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 6 edition of RAW, Mr. McMahon gave Masters & Carlito   │
   │    this opportunity as a reward for Masters helping him with Marty     │
   │    Jannetty the week before on RAW. That night, they responded by      │
   │    attacking Kane during his WrestleMania rewind match with Triple H;  │
   │    after Carlito spit his apple in the Big Red Monster's face, he &    │
   │    Masters ran him into the steel ring post.                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    They tried to attack Big Show later in the night, but Kane ran out  │
   │    to stop them before they could reach his partner.                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    This won't be the first time the two teams have met for the gold;   │
   │    on RAW the night after the Royal Rumble, Kane & Show beat Carlito   │
   │    & Masters to retain the World Tag Team Championship.                │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The two teams were at odds on the March 13 edition of RAW as well.  │
   │    Big Show & Kane came out at the tail end of the John Cena and HHH   │
   │    contract signing, & they were soon attacked by Carlito and Masters. │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Since everyone seemed so eager to fight, Mr. McMahon set up a six   │
   │    man tag team match for later on RAW - WWE Champion John Cena, Kane  │
   │    & Big Show vs Triple H, Carlito & Chris Masters. Not too long after │
   │    the match began, Carlito and Masters grabbed a couple of steel      │
   │    chairs and nailed Big Show & Kane.                                  │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week, the two teams were matched up in singles        │
   │    competition, with the partners banned from ringside for both        │
   │    matches. In the first bout, Kane quickly defeated Carlito after     │
   │    a chokeslam, causing Carlito to blow up at Masters. The Masterpiece │
   │    said he had a plan, and later in the night it came to fruition;     │
   │    Big Show defeated Masters by DQ, but it was a result of Masters     │
   │    nailing him twice with a steel chair. After the match, The          │
   │    Masterpiece ran Big Show into the steel ringpost as well.           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 27 RAW, Carlito requested a rematch with Kane. It      │
   │    turned out to be a trap, as Carlito got himself disqualified. When  │
   │    Kane cahsed him to the back, Lance Cade, Trevor Murdoch & Masters   │
   │    were waiting to attack. They tried to lock Kane behind a door       │
   │    barricaded with a forklift, but the room Kane was in had a back     │
   │    door, and the Big Red Monster was able to easily escape.            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    That same night, Big Show was set to take the Master Lock Challenge │
   │    and with their earlier plan backfiring, Kane ran Carlito away from  │
   │    ringside. Masters couldn't get his Master Lock on Big Show, so he   │
   │    attacked the big man instead. Big Show fought him off, eventually   │
   │    leaving "The Masterpiece" laying in the ring after a thunderous     │
   │    chokeslam.                                                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Can Carlito & Masters overcome the much bigger team of Kane & Big   │
   │    Show at WrestleMania 22, or will Big Show & Kane continue their     │
   │    amazing stretch of dominance in the RAW tag team division?          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                          Women's Championship                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                 Champion Trish Stratus Vs Mickie James                 │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    For months, Mickie James claimed to be Trish Stratus' biggest fan,  │
   │    going so far as to proclaim her love for Trish on several occasions │
   │    Thanks to a brutal attack on Saturday Night's Main Event, it seems  │
   │    the love is gone, and now at WrestleMania 22, James will take on    │
   │    her idol for the Women's Championship.                              │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Last fall, James made her debut on RAW, helping Trish & Ashley fend │
   │    off an attack from Victoria. (Watch video) She said she was Trish's │
   │    No. 1 fan, and did anything and everything to help Trish succeed,   │
   │    even seemingly sacrificing herself to help Trish win the Fulfill    │
   │    Your Fantasy Battle Royal at Taboo Tuesday. James even dressed up   │
   │    as Trish for Halloween, complete with replica Women's Championship. │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Shortly before Christmas, Mickie decided to profess her love for    │
   │    Trish in the locker room. The 2 were standing underneath mistletoe, │
   │    & Mickie tried to kiss Trish; the Women's Champion seemed flustered │
   │    and walked away, leaving Mickie confused. Mickie apologized, but    │
   │    for the first time it seemed there was something more to their      │
   │    relationship, at least in Mickie's mind.                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    At New Year's Revolution, Trish defeated Mickie to retain the       │
   │    Women's Championship, but Mickie seemed happy just to have the      │
   │    opportunity to be in the ring with Trish. From there, her behavior  │
   │    became continually more aggressive until Trish had enough.          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 6 edition of RAW, Trish told Mickie that they needed   │
   │    to spend some time apart, because her behavior was too much to take.│
   │    Mickie seemed crushed but agreed to Trish's request. The next week, │
   │    an attack on Torrie left Trish without a partner for Saturday       │
   │    Night's Main Event. Mickie volunteered to fill in, saying she would │
   │    respect Trish's wishes to go their separate ways after the match.   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Trish agreed, and when Saturday Night's Main Event rolled around,   │
   │    the two were victorious over Candice & Victoria. After the match,   │
   │    Mickie wanted to say goodbye to Trish the proper way, and leaned    │
   │    in to try to kiss the Women's Champion. After Trish pulled away,    │
   │    a crestfallen Mickie nailed her idol with a Mick Kick and laid her  │
   │    out with her own version of Stratusfaction. Later on WWE.com        │
   │    Unlimited, Mickie said she dedicated her life to Trish, but not     │
   │    once did Trish appreciate her. Mickie said Trish broke her heart,   │
   │    and now she would break Trish.                                      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following Monday on RAW, Mickie claimed to have a gift for      │
   │    Trish. As Trish came down to claim it, Mickie revealed a bound &    │
   │    gagged Ashley as the surprise. An angered Trish quickly attacked    │
   │    Mickie, but as the Women's Champion stopped to help her abducted    │
   │    friend, Mickie attacked from behind, leaving Trish laying in the    │
   │    ring after a vicious Tornado DDT.                                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, Mickie had one last message   │
   │    for Trish. Prior to her match with Torrie against Candice &         │
   │    Victoria, Trish saw the message on a television monitor. Sitting    │
   │    in a room filled with pictures of Trish, Mickie told the Women's    │
   │    Champion that while she used to be Trish's No. 1 Fan, her new       │
   │    obsession was Trishs demise. She then tore up a picture to emphasize│
   │    her point. (Watch video) Trish shook off the disturbing footage to  │
   │    still pick up a tag team win with Torrie.                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    So at WrestleMania 22, Mickie will get her chance to take the one   │
   │    thing Trish values most, the Women's Championship. Can she topple   │
   │    the most decorated Women's Champion in history and walk out with    │
   │    the gold, or will Trish put Mickie in her place once and for all?   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                    Boogeyman Vs Booker T & Sharmell                    │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    For weeks, Booker T and his wife Sharmell have been haunted by the  │
   │    bizarre Boogeyman. Everywhere Booker and Sharmell turn, the worm    │
   │    eating Superstar is right behind them. Booker T demanded that       │
   │    General Manager Theodore Long put a stop to Boogeyman, but instead, │
   │    Long left that up to Booker T and set up a match for Saturday       │
   │    Night's Main Event.                                                 │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The match, however, never even happened. While in the back          │
   │    receiving medical attention, Booker T explained to Long that he     │
   │    heard something pop in his knee earlier in the day. The only way    │
   │    to see what the real extent of the injury was would be with an MRI. │
   │    The only problem, though, is that an MRI would take well over a few │
   │    hours to obtain. So, going along with the doctor's opinion, Long    │
   │    canceled the match. Booker T limped out of the room, but a smile    │
   │    briefly crept across his face in between yelps of pain.             │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Later on in the show, Booker T was getting out of the shower, and   │
   │    he and Sharmell were talking about how they had duped Long. Booker  │
   │    was never injured. He just wanted out of the match, and the five    │
   │    time WCW Champion had gotten his way. Booker T even did a little    │
   │    dance, showing no signs of a knee injury. Then all of a sudden,     │
   │    Boogeyman's music hit and the worm-eating Superstar lowered himself │
   │    down from the ceiling. Booker T, only dressed in a towel, and       │
   │    Sharmell, who didn't have a shirt on yet, screamed out in terror    │
   │    and ran out of the room.                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Booker T may have gotten his way, but the satisfaction will only be │
   │    momentary. Long decided that match will go on û at WrestleMania 22. │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    The following week on Friday Night SmackDown, Long had Booker sign  │
   │    the contract for the match. He initially refused, but Long said that│
   │    he would be fired if he didn't sign. The General Manager did allow  │
   │    Booker a partner, and once Booker signed the contract, he said he   │
   │    didn't care who his partner was. With that, Long announced that     │
   │    Booker's partner would be none other than his wife, Sharmell.       │
   │    Booker & Sharmell were horrified, but the contract had already      │
   │    been signed.                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Boogeyman continued to haunt Booker T and Sharmell during the last  │
   │    stop on the Road to WrestleMania 22 on SmackDown. Booker went one   │
   │    on one with the swashbuckling Paul Burchill, but during the match,  │
   │    Boogeyman's music hit and the arena began to fill with the          │
   │    mysterious red smoke. Booker and Sharmell were immediately          │
   │    horrified, and Booker left the ring. He went underneath the ring    │
   │    to look for the worm-eating Superstar, but when he did so, Boogeyman│
   │    emerged from under the ring and hoisted Sharmell over his shoulders │
   │    and took her to the back. Booker T went after his wife and followed │
   │    a trail of worms all the way into the bowels of Kemper Arena. He    │
   │    finally found his wife, and a huge pile of worms, and carried her   │
   │    to safety.                                                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    But there will be nowhere to run to at WrestleMania 22. Can the     │
   │    husband and wife face their fears on April 2 to be successful?      │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │· ··--─-─-────────────────────────────────────────────────────-─-─--·· ·│
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │                          Playboy Pillow Fight                          │
   │                                                                        │
   │                   Torrie Wilson Vs. Candice Michelle                   │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    In recent weeks, the friendship between Candice Michelle & Torrie   │
   │    Wilson has disintegrated. At WrestleMania 22, the current Playboy   │
   │    Magazine cover girl and the former two-time Playboy model will      │
   │    settle their differences in a Playboy Pillow Fight.                 │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    Tensions began to mount between the two on the Feb. 16 edition of   │
   │    RAW. After Torrie's loss to Ashley, Candice attempted to cheer her  │
   │    up by announcing the upcoming release of her Playboy pictorial.     │
   │    Things were made worse two weeks later when Candice blamed Torrie   │
   │    for her loss to Women's Champion Trish Stratus, even slapping       │
   │    Torrie in the face during WWE.com Unlimited. (Watch video) As the   │
   │    launch of Candice's issue of Playboy came near, Candice became      │
   │    more and more arrogant, repeatedly telling Torrie that she was the  │
   │    hottest WWE Diva to ever pose in Playboy.                           │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the March 6 edition of RAW, Candice revealed her Playboy cover   │
   │    to the world. Then, in a shocking moment, after Torrie took offense │
   │    to Candice's statements, Candice had Victoria attack Torrie from    │
   │    behind. Victoria & Candice left Torrie beaten in the ring, breaking │
   │    up their friendship for good.                                       │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    It was announced the next week that Torrie would team with Trish    │
   │    Stratus to face Candice & Victoria at Saturday Night's Main Event   │
   │    but Torrie was mysteriously knocked out backstage on RAW. An        │
   │    autographed copy of Candice's Playboy was found at the scene, & the │
   │    attack left Torrie unable to participate in the scheduled match.    │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    That Monday on RAW, Torrie took on Victoria. As the match began,    │
   │    Candice made a grand entrance, coming out on a bed caried by four   │
   │    men. She then proceeded to throw pillows at Torrie as a distraction │
   │    it worked, as Victoria was able to hit the Widow's Peak on Torrie   │
   │    for the quick victory. After the match, Candice hit Torrie with a   │
   │    pillow for good measure.                                            │
   │                                                                        │
   │                                                                        │
   │    On the final RAW before WrestleMania, Torrie got a measure of       │
   │    revenge when she teamed with Trish Stratus to defeat Candice &      │
   │    Victoria. On April 2, Torrie will have one more chance to get her   │
   │    hands on Candice. Can she shut Candice up once & for all or will    │
   │    the Candy-licious Diva prove to be too hot for WrestleMania?        │
   │                                                                        │
